    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-01-11T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-11T16:00:00-05:00" n="52"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                    Indochina/1–1148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bonsal</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-01-11T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 11, 1948—10 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Foreign Minister<note n="1" xml:id="d52fn1">Dr. C. G. W. H. Baron van
                        Boetzelaer van Oosterhout.</note> has just informed me that Cabinet this
                    afternoon authorized Dutch delegation <hi rend="italic">Renville</hi> accept 6
                    points for political settlement offered by <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss>
                    representing slight modification of points set forth January 9 to Helb by
                    Department officials (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 9, January
                        9).<note n="2" xml:id="d52fn2">See telegram 10, January 9, 6 p. m., <ref
                            target="#pg_70">p. 70</ref>, and Batavia telegram 22, January 6, 5 p.
                        m., <ref target="#pg_62">p. 62</ref>.</note> Necessary authority telegraphed
                    Batavia. Van Kleffens will inform Department.<note n="3" xml:id="d52fn3">The
                        Netherlands Embassy telephoned the information on January 12 to the
                        Department. (856e.00/l–1248)</note> Foreign Minister states Netherlands
                    acceptance predicated on signature truce agreement and its thorough-going
                    implementation by Republic. Netherland Government has doubts re feasibility
                    provisions in 6 points relating plebiscites and representation in <gloss
                        target="#t_USI1">USI</gloss> accordance population. Cabinet unhappy at
                    reference (reported by Helb) by Department officials in conversation with Helb
                    to <gloss target="#t_ERP1">ERP</gloss> and to US assistance in reconstruction
                    Indonesia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonsal</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
